ereas, Jim was an active member of the Republican Party and held the office of President of the Wyoming County Republican Committee in the 1990s; andWhereas, Jim was a Godly man who expressed his love for the Lord through music ministry; andWhereas, Jim was a lifelong member of Matheny Methodist Church, a devoted family man, wonderful husband to Karen Cline Sigmon, and loving father to Molly Sigmon-Toney and Chloe Sigmon; andWhereas, Jim received his heavenly healing and went to be with the Lord on June 4, 2015; andWhereas, It is fitting that an enduring memorial be established to commemorate James "Jim" Sigmon, Jr. and his contributions to our state and country; therefore, be it Resolved by the Legislature of West Virginia:That the Division of Highways is hereby requested to name bridge number: (55A106), (37.69680, -81.52925), locally known as the Laurel Fork Bridge, carrying Mabel Street over Glen Fork in Wyoming County, the "Jim Sigmon Family Memorial Bridge"; and, be it Further Resolved, That the Division of Highways is hereby requested to have made and be placed signs at both ends identifying the bridge as the "Jim Sigmon Family Memorial Bridge"; and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk of the House is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the Commissioner of the Division of Highways. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: